234 - Palindrome Linked List
Problem Statement

Given the head of a singly linked list, return true if the linked list is a palindrome, otherwise return false.

A palindrome reads the same forward and backward.

Example
Input:  1 -> 2 -> 2 -> 1
Output: true

Input:  1 -> 2
Output: false
Approach

The optimal solution uses three steps:

1. Find the Middle of the Linked List

Use the Slow and Fast Pointer technique.

slow moves one step.
fast moves two steps.

When the loop ends, slow will be at the middle of the list.

while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {
    slow = slow.next;
    fast = fast.next.next;
}
2. Reverse the Second Half

Starting from slow, reverse the remaining part of the linked list.

ListNode prev = null;

while (slow != null) {
    ListNode next = slow.next;
    slow.next = prev;
    prev = slow;
    slow = next;
}

After reversal, prev becomes the head of the reversed second half.

3. Compare Both Halves

Use two pointers:

left starts from the head.
right starts from the reversed second half.

Compare values one by one.

while (right != null) {

    if (left.val != right.val) {
        return false;
    }

    left = left.next;
    right = right.next;
}

If all values match, the linked list is a palindrome.

Algorithm
Handle edge cases (null or single node).
Find the middle using slow and fast pointers.
Reverse the second half of the list.
Compare the first half with the reversed second half.
If any mismatch occurs, return false.
Otherwise, return true.
Code
class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(ListNode head) {

        if (head == null || head.next == null) {
            return true;
        }

        ListNode slow = head;
        ListNode fast = head;

        while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {
            slow = slow.next;
            fast = fast.next.next;
        }

        ListNode prev = null;

        while (slow != null) {
            ListNode next = slow.next;
            slow.next = prev;
            prev = slow;
            slow = next;
        }

        ListNode left = head;
        ListNode right = prev;

        while (right != null) {

            if (left.val != right.val) {
                return false;
            }

            left = left.next;
            right = right.next;
        }

        return true;
    }
}
